South African lender FirstRand said on Thursday its half-year profits would likely be up to 25% lower, as the impact of the coronavirus crisis continues to hurt operations. Still, it said, the first four months of its financial year had been better than expected, though it warned it remained “cautious about the sustainability of this rebound”. Black Friday SpecialGet 15% discount on our annual subscription!
